It would be safer to use the UUID for the concept ("1284AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA") since we don't want to be relying on a concept having a given concept id (i.e., we don't want to rely on a dictionary having IDs in a certain order). Even better might be to just be to leverage the system for CIEL and the concept ID, via something like:
TokenAndListParam problemList = new TokenAndListParam();
		problemList.addAnd(new TokenParam().setSystem("https://openconceptlab.org/orgs/CIEL/sources/CIEL").setValue("1284"));
		handleCodeableConcept(criteria, problemList, "c", "cm", "crt");
Then this "1284" string would have a place in the FhirConstants file.

